Class GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.builders.propertyvalue.typed.GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBuilder<ComplexPropertyValue>

    public final class GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder
extends Object
implements IBuilder<ComplexPropertyValue>
    An IBuilder for creating ComplexPropertyValues that contain values of type LogicalType.GEOSPATIAL.
    Since:
    5.0

      • setToCoordinates

        public GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder setToCoordinates(short latitude,
                                                       short longitude)
        Sets all parts of the value in this GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder from the specified latitude and longitude.

        The method sets the WGS84 and machine-readable latitude and longitude to the specified values, and the spatial reference authority and the SRID to those for WGS84.

        Parameters:
        latitude - The latitude in degrees, which must be in the range -90 to 90.
        longitude - The longitude in degrees, which must be in the range -180 to 180.
        Returns:
        This GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder.

      • setSpatialReferenceSystem

        public GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder setSpatialReferenceSystem(String issuingAuthoirty,
                                                                int srid)
        Sets the part of the value in this GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder that contains the identifier and issuing authority of the spatial reference system from the specified values.
        Parameters:
        issuingAuthoirty - A String that contains the name of the issuing authority of the spatial reference system in which the machine-readable latitude and longitude are to be interpreted.
        srid - The identifier of the spatial reference system in which the machine-readable latitude and longitude are to be interpreted.

        This GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder.

      • populate

        public GeospatialPropertyValueBuilder populate(ComplexPropertyValue values)
        Description copied from interface: IBuilder
        Populates the data in the builder from an object of the same type that the builder creates.

        Assuming an implementation of T.equals(), then after this statement:

        t2 = builder.populate(t1).build();

        The following expressions should both evaluate to true:

        t2.equals(t1) == true
        (t2 == t1) == false

        Specified by:
        populate in interface IBuilder<ComplexPropertyValue>
        Parameters:
        values - The object from which to populate the builder.
        Returns:
        The builder, populated with the data from the specified object.
